                <persName role="author">M. Putzel</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Easton</placeName>, <date>May 2th 1848</date>.</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I understand that the German Kehilla<lb/> in
                    <placeName>Phila</placeName> should be occupied by a Hazan<lb/> I
                    quit<add>?</add> at my congregation here and should be glad<lb/> to get another
                position. If you have any influence at the <add>◊©◊ï◊ó◊ò</add>
                <add>Kahal</add> there, you would oblige me by recommending<lb/> me there. I am
                prepared to act as Hazan, Sohet<lb/> teacher and preacher.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><del>
                    <add>?</add>
                </del> Being grateful for whatever you<lb/> will do for me, I am,</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">Very truly yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">M. Putzel</p>
            <p><placeName>Easton</placeName>, <date><hi rend="underline">May 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi>
                        1848</hi></date></p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>, <placeName>Phila.</placeName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Easton</placeName>, <date>May 2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi>
                    1848</date></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir:</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">The Jewish congregation Brith Shalom<lb/> of this town asks me to
                propose the following to<lb/> the family <persName>Hart</persName> using you as an
                agent.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">During the last winter the<lb/> congregation informed <persName>Mrs.
                    Hart</persName> that <del>she</del> it had<lb/> bought a place for a cemetery
                and that she<lb/> should return the key for the old cemetery</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>If however, <persName>Mrs. Hart</persName> is willing to give the<lb/> congregation a
                deed for it, then the congregation is ready<lb/> to order a Pavement (?) as is
                required by the<lb/>
                <sic>Burrough</sic> Council. This will involve a cost of<lb/> about $50.‚Äî The
                congregation has this (same)<lb/> opinion and desires a definite answer by
                return<lb/> mail.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Very truly yours,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName role="author">Michael Putzel</persName>, Secy</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">of the Brith Shalom</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">congregation at <placeName>Easton</placeName></p>
            <p rend="The following is written in the left margin.">for <persName>Mrs.
                    Hart</persName></p>
            <pb n="5"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philda.</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>Rev. Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please accept this note below for to advertise in the<lb/> Occident
                in the <date>March</date> Edition. Bearer of this will pay<lb/> the fees.‚Äî After the
                Dedication of our new <sic>Synagoge</sic> I<lb/> shall take the liberty to send you
                some remarks about it<lb/> for publication in your beloved Paper.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Yours Sirs<add>?</add> most obedient servant</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">Michael Putzel</persName><add>?</add>,
                Pres.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">of the Congr. EmanuEl.</p>
            <pb n="6"/>
